article.headline: New York 56, Charlotte 48
article.linkText: Johnson's career-high 27 helps Liberty snap skid
article.story:
NEW YORK (AP) -- Vickie Johnson tied her career high with 27 points to help the New York Liberty snap a three-game losing streak with a 56-48 victory over the Charlotte Sting on Friday night. Johnson even played point guard when New York (8-8) needed a boost. Johnson scored eight points during a 10-2 run in the second half that gave the Liberty the lead for good. Tari Phillips added 13 rebounds, seven points and three blocks for New York. Shalonda Enis added 15 points and 10 rebounds, and Dawn Staley had 13 points and seven assists for Charlotte (12-8), which lost its second straight after winning four in a row before the All-Star break. Staley head-faked Teresa Weatherspoon and hit an open jumper to put the Sting up 39-35 with 12:53 left, but then Johnson took over. The Liberty guard hit two 3-pointers and drove for a nifty layup, and Tamika Whitmore added a layup as New York went up 45-41. The Liberty never lost the lead. With Weatherspoon and backup point guard Kristen Sharp on the bench, Johnson even guided the offense by bringing the ball up the court. Her slick layup with 2:23 left put New York up 52-46, and the Sting were forced to foul. The Sting shot just 23 percent from the field in the first half, but the Liberty never managed more than a nine-point lead. Charlotte hit five free throws in a row to get within 21-17, but New York took a 29-21 lead into halftime.
Game notes
Both teams lost to Washington this week after the Mystics had lost 11 straight games. ... The Sting scored only seven points in the first 7:11 of the first half, then went 7:11 without another field goal. ... Enis left the game after nearly fainting in the Sting's huddle about four minutes into the second half. She returned five minutes later. ... Liberty coach Richie Adubato was called for a technical during the Liberty's second-half drought, and Charlotte's Trudy Lacey slapped a bottle of resin in the first half, spraying it all over the security guard near the Sting's bench.
